      • executeForReceipt

        @Deprecated
public final TransactionReceipt executeForReceipt()
                                                       throws HederaException,
                                                              HederaNetworkException
        Deprecated. Makes it difficult to discern whether an error occurred while executing or while fetching a receipt. Call HederaCall.execute(Client) then getReceipt(Client) and handle the errors separately from each.
        Execute this transaction and wait for its receipt to be generated.

        If the receipt does not become available after a few seconds, HederaException is thrown.

        Returns:
        the receipt for the transaction
        Throws:
        HederaException - for any response code that is not ResponseCodeEnum.SUCCESS
        HederaNetworkException
        RuntimeException - if an InterruptedException is thrown while waiting for the receipt.

      • executeForRecord

        @Deprecated
public TransactionRecord executeForRecord()
                                               throws HederaException,
                                                      HederaNetworkException
        Deprecated. Makes it difficult to discern whether an error occurred while executing or while fetching a record. Call HederaCall.execute(Client) then getRecord(Client) and handle the errors separately from each.
        Execute this transaction and wait for its record to be generated.

        If the record does not become available after a few seconds, HederaException is thrown.

        Returns:
        the receipt for the transaction
        Throws:
        HederaException - for any response code that is not ResponseCodeEnum.SUCCESS
        HederaNetworkException
        RuntimeException - if an InterruptedException is thrown while waiting for the receipt.
